text: POP3 and secure POP are allowed by the University firewall
HTTP and HTTPS are allowed by the University firewall
You may not run FTP, telnet, peer-to-peer, HTTP, IRC, DNS and mail servers on ResNet or UIC wireless-connected devices
There is a 6 GB per 24-hour period upload or download data transfer limit starting at midnight of each day, on all of your combined traffic on ResNet and UIC wireless
P2P application is separately capped at 30 Mbps for the entire campus
CounterStrike server is blocked by the University firewall
SSH is allowed by the University firewall
Internet is limited to 3 Mbps per host
Telnet is allowed by the University firewall
You may not run any services (e.g., FTP services,listservers,P2P file sharing servers, publishing files via generic file services, etc.) via ResNet or NYURoam wireless networks
Net2Phone is allowed by the University firewall
The ResNet cap is currently 200 gigabytes per each 7 day period of combined incoming and outgoing traffic
